course_mapping: Course MATH 005A (Single Variable Calculus I) at Pasadena City College must be taken to satisfy course MATH 1A (Calculus) at University of California, Berkeley for the computer science major.

Course MATH 005B (Single Variable Calculus II) and MATH 055 (Differential Equations) at Pasadena City College must be taken to satisfy course MATH 1B (Calculus) at University of California, Berkeley for the computer science major.

Course MATH 010 (Linear Algebra and Applications) and MATH 055 (Differential Equations) at Pasadena City College must be taken to satisfy course MATH 54 (Linear Algebra and Differential Equations) at University of California, Berkeley for the computer science major.

Course ENGR 016 (Engineering Circuits) and ENGR 016L (Engineering Circuits Laboratory) and MATH 010 (Linear Algebra and Applications) at Pasadena City College must be taken to satisfy course EECS 16A (Designing Information Devices and Systems I) at University of California, Berkeley for the computer science major.

Course MATH 010 (Linear Algebra and Applications) and MATH 055 (Differential Equations) at Pasadena City College must be taken to satisfy course MATH 54 (Linear Algebra and Differential Equations) at University of California, Berkeley for the computer science major.

Course MATH 010 (Linear Algebra and Applications) and MATH 055 (Differential Equations) or ENGR 016 (Engineering Circuits) and ENGR 016L (Engineering Circuits Laboratory) and MATH 010 (Linear Algebra and Applications) at Pasadena City College must be taken to satisfy either MATH 54 (Linear Algebra and Differential Equations) or EECS 16A (Designing Information Devices and Systems I) at University of California, Berkeley for the computer science major.
